definitions.definition: ( food , loosely ) Any of various hard-shelled seeds or hard, dry fruits from various families of plants .
examples: There are many sorts of nuts : pea nuts , cashews, pistachios, Brazil nuts and more.

subdefinitions.definition: ( botany , strictly ) Such a fruit that is indehiscent .

definitions.definition: ( hardware ) A piece of hardware , typically metal and typically hexagonal or square in shape, with a hole through it having internal screw threads , intended to be screwed onto a threaded bolt or other threaded shaft .

examples: He was driving his car like a nut .
a fashion nut — a gun nut — a sailing nut

definitions.definition: ( UK , Ireland , slang , dated ) An extravagantly fashionable young man. [1910s–1920s]
( anatomy ) Senses related to male genitalia.

subdefinitions.definition: ( archaic ) The glans ( structure at the extremity of the penis or of the clitoris ) .
( vulgar , slang , chiefly plural ) A testicle .
examples: I kicked him in the nuts .

subdefinitions.definition: ( vulgar , slang , uncountable ) Semen , ejaculate , cum .
( vulgar , slang , countable ) Orgasm , ejaculation ; especially release of semen ; cumshot
examples: He just needs a good nut to make himself feel better.

definitions.definition: ( US , slang ) Monthly expense to keep a venture running.
( US , slang ) The amount of money necessary to set up some venture; set-up costs.
( US , slang ) A stash of money owned by an extremely rich investor , sufficient to sustain a high level of consumption if all other money is lost.

( music , lutherie ) On stringed instruments such as guitars and violins, the small piece at the peghead end of the fingerboard that holds the strings at the proper spacing and, in most cases, the proper height.
( typography slang ) En , a unit of measurement equal to half of the height of the type in use.

( climbing ) A shaped piece of metal, threaded by a wire loop, which is jammed in a crack in the rockface and used to protect a climb. (Originally, machine nuts [sense #2] were used for this purpose.)
( poker , attributive ) The best possible hand of a certain type. Compare nuts ( “ the best possible hand available ” ) .
examples: nut straight , nut flush , nut full house

definitions.definition: ( firearms ) The tumbler of a gunlock .
( nautical ) A projection on each side of the shank of an anchor , to secure the stock in place.
( archaic except in combination with a modifier ) A small rounded cake or cookie .
